    {
      "id": "1136887663174103190",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2023-08-04T00:05:41.252-05:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "All : we had this list of questions in a prev \"Chat with a leader\" session. LMK if this is a good list or if we should discuss something else as well? Obv, we won't be able to go thru all of these with 4-5 leaders, so I might have to prioritize as well. \n\nCan you tell us more about your TPM journey?\n1) Can you talk us through a day in the life of a Director of Product TPM?\n2) How do you keep your technical skills current?\n3) How much weight do you put on Technical Domain Knowledge vs Program Management as a hiring manager for TPM roles?\n4) For senior roles, how do you look at depth vs breath for a TPM?  If you had to pick, which do you find more important?\n5) If I'm joining your organization as a new TPM, what are the top 3 things to focus on in the first 30/60/90 days to create impact?\n6) What makes a great candidate, great?  What are the things you look for in interviews?\n7) If you could time travel, what advice will you give to your younger self, especially when you started your career as a TPM?\n8) What did it take for you to be ready to be promoted from an IC to Manager and Manager to Director?\n9) What's your advice for juggling multiple programs at once?  How do you know when to go deep on one while still balancing the others?\n10) How should TPMs influence technical decisions in a program?  Do you have an example where you did this well?\n11) Could you explain the interview process at LinkedIn?\n12) How does one advance to more senior levels (L7+) as an IC?\n13) How do I determine if I am really feeling an imposter syndrome, or I am struggling in a new job?  Any recommendations on how to overcome imposter syndrome?\n14) How would you describe the culture and work/life balance in your team?  Is there anything you'd want to change about it?\n15) How is your and your team's WLB?  What are signs you look for to help proactively prevent burnout?\n16) What recommendations and strategies can you share on growing a team, could be TPM or other?",
      "author": {
