    {
      "id": "1185703438714146816",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2023-12-16T16:02:09.094-06:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "I feel that Data Scientists/ Analysts / TPMs are only good as entry points to any FAANG company. These roles are not strategic decision making roles and therefore, all the credit for their work goes to PMs/ EMs, EVEN if they moved the needle in any project. Also, they can easily be made scapegoats in case of wrong decisions.\n\nIts just how it works. Therefore, if one wishes to be a people manager soon and advance to VP levels, Product / Engineering Management are the right tracks. There are plenty of growth opportunities and companies need people to grow in these skillsets",
      "author": {
        "id": "456226577798135808",
        "name": "Deleted User",
        "discriminator": "0000",
